Aldar, Batelco, Kuwait Finance: Persian Gulf Equity Preview

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-09-29T05:12:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/aldar-and-kuwait-finance-house-persian-gulf-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Persian Gulf stock markets. Symbols are in parentheses
and prices are from last close.  Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  fell for a third day this
week, losing 0.4 percent. Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  dropped 0.7
percent. Saudi Arabia’s market is closed for the weekend.  Aldar Properties PJSC (ALDAR)  : Abu Dhabi’s biggest real-
estate company will focus on completing projects and handing
over units to owners in 2012, Chief Executive Officer Sami Asad
said. The shares were unchanged at 1.18 dirhams.  Bahrain Telecom Co. (BATELCO)  : Bahrain’s largest phone
company said it won’t proceed with an offer to acquire 25
percent of Mobile Telecommunications Co. of Saudi Arabia. The
shares were unchanged at 0.398 dinar. Mobile Telecommunications
Co. (ZAIN KK) gained 1 percent to 970 fils in Kuwait City
trading.  Kuwait Finance House (KFIN)  : The Kuwait-based financial
services company obtained approval for a six-month extension on
a 10 percent share buyback. The shares were unchanged at 910
fils.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
